Paul Simonon came up with the band's name, The Clash, after they had considered alternatives including "The Weak Heartdrops" and "The Psychotic Negatives".<ref>Topping 2004, p. 12.</ref><ref name="MTV-Rockumentary" /> Simonon explained how he came up with the name, "It really came to my head when I start reading the newspapers and a word that kept recurring was the word 'clash', so I thought 'the Clash, what about that,' to the others. And they and Bernard they went for it."<ref name="MTV-Rockumentary" /> After deciding on a name, the band found a stable drummer in [[Terry Chimes]]. 

The Clash had their first gig on [[July 4]], [[1976]], supporting the [[Sex Pistols]] at the Black Swan in [[Sheffield]].<ref name="Gray-Last_Gang_in_Town" /><ref name="Westway_to_the_World" /><ref>{{cite web 
 | url = http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1470448/20030310/clash.jhtml 
