 | first = Kurt 
 | date = 2003-03-13 
 | publisher = MTV News 
 | quote = The London SS changed their name to the Clash, and made their debut opening for the Sex Pistols at a gig on July 4, 1976. 
}}</ref> By that autumn the band had signed a contract with [[Columbia Records|CBS Records]].<ref name="Westway_to_the_World" /><ref name="Jaffee-The_Politics_of_Rock">{{cite book
